  <!-- WINDOWS & DOORS -->
  <section class="windows-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Windows & Doors:<br><span class="text-gold">European Engineering Excellence</span></h2>
      
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-card large">
          <h3>Tilt & Turn Mechanism</h3>
          <p>Unlike American sliding or single-hung windows, European tilt-and-turn windows offer two opening modes:</p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>Tilt mode:</strong> Top tilts inward for ventilation while maintaining security and weather protection</li>
            <li><strong>Turn mode:</strong> Entire window swings inward like a door for easy cleaning and maximum airflow</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Triple Glazing</h3>
          <p>Three panes of glass with argon gas fill provide superior insulation compared to standard American double-pane windows.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>PVC Frames</h3>
          <p>High-quality PVC frames with steel reinforcement won't warp, rot, or require painting. Lifespan: 50+ years.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Multi-Point Locking</h3>
          <p>3-5 locking points around the frame provide exceptional security and create an airtight seal when closed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Table -->
      <div class="table-container">
        <h3>Window Performance Comparison</h3>
        <table class="comparison-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Feature</th>
              <th>American Standard</th>
              <th>European Premium</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>U-Factor (Heat Transfer)</td>
              <td>0.30 - 0.50</td>
              <td>0.14 - 0.20 ⭐</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>SHGC (Solar Heat Gain)</td>
              <td>0.25 - 0.40</td>
              <td>0.20 - 0.30 ⭐</td>
