      <div class="materials-grid">
        <div class="material-card">
          <div class="material-icon">🧱</div>
          <h3>Cement Stucco</h3>
          <p>Unlike American acrylic stucco over foam, European cement-based stucco is applied in multiple coats over wire mesh, creating a rock-hard, breathable finish that lasts 50+ years without cracking.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="material-card">
          <div class="material-icon">🪨</div>
          <h3>Natural Stone</h3>
          <p>Granite, limestone, and slate provide timeless beauty and unmatched durability. Unlike manufactured stone veneer, natural stone won't fade, crack, or lose its value over decades.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="material-card">
          <div class="material-icon">🏗️</div>
          <h3>Reinforced Concrete</h3>
          <p>Floors and roofs made with reinforced concrete slabs provide superior sound insulation, fire resistance, and structural integrity compared to wood joists and drywall ceilings.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="material-card">
          <div class="material-icon">🚫</div>
          <h3>No Drywall</h3>
          <p>European homes use cement plaster over masonry, eliminating the mold-prone drywall common in American construction. Result: better air quality and walls that can't be punched through.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

