    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Built for Texas Weather:<br><span class="text-gold">Hurricane & Storm Ready</span></h2>
      
      <div class="resistance-grid">
        <div class="resistance-card">
          <div class="resistance-icon">🌀</div>
          <h3>Hurricane Resistance</h3>
          <p>Concrete block and reinforced concrete walls can withstand Category 5 hurricane winds (157+ mph) without structural damage. Impact-resistant windows protect against flying debris.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="resistance-card">
          <div class="resistance-icon">🌊</div>
          <h3>Flood Protection</h3>
          <p>Masonry construction doesn't absorb water like wood framing. After flooding, concrete structures can be cleaned and restored without requiring complete wall replacement.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="resistance-card">
          <div class="resistance-icon">🔥</div>
          <h3>Fire Safety</h3>
          <p>Concrete and masonry are non-combustible, providing superior fire resistance. European homes have significantly lower fire insurance premiums due to reduced risk.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="resistance-card">
          <div class="resistance-icon">🌡️</div>
          <h3>Extreme Heat</h3>
          <p>Thermal mass of concrete walls absorbs heat during the day and releases it slowly at night, naturally regulating indoor temperatures and reducing AC dependency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Hurricane Stats -->
      <div class="hurricane-stats">
        <div class="stat-highlight">
